00:09:54.660 --> 00:09:57.240
tried in the past,
and historically they

00:09:57.240 --> 00:10:00.480
have not been great or
they have been killed.

00:10:00.480 --> 00:10:03.360
And I want to be
able to see, like,

00:10:03.360 --> 00:10:08.430
a version of iMessage that could
come to Android that is either

00:10:08.430 --> 00:10:12.090
supported and continued
to be built upon

00:10:12.090 --> 00:10:15.000
or is agreed upon by all the
OEMs that necessarily do it.

00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:19.110
