of an interesting discussion

00:23:44.990 --> 00:23:45.490
point.

00:23:45.490 --> 00:23:48.060
With regards to a device
like the Samsung Galaxy Fold,

00:23:48.060 --> 00:23:49.790
who starts that conversation?

00:23:49.790 --> 00:23:51.560
Is it Samsung or Google?

00:23:51.560 --> 00:23:53.720
Like hey, we'd like to
build a folded device.

00:23:53.720 --> 00:23:56.597
Any chance you can support
bendy phones in the OS?

00:23:56.597 --> 00:23:57.718
AUDIENCE: [LAUGHING]

00:23:57.718 --> 00:23:58.760
DAVE BURKE: Bendy phones?

00:23:58.760 --> 00:23:59.802
CHET HAASE: Bendy phones.

00:23:59.802 --> 00:24:01.460
DAVE BURKE: Bendy phones.

00:24:01.460 --> 00:24:04.010
You know, what I've
noticed in the last decade,

00:24:04.010 --> 00:24:07.190
the way this goes is really it's
actually the supply chain that

00:24:07.190 --> 00:24:10.250
comes up with some technology,
whether it's like a fingerprint

00:24:10.250 --> 00:24:16.750
sensor or folded, bendable
displays, flexible displays.

00:24:16.750 --> 00:24:19.200
And the supply chain
puts it out there.

00:24:19.200 --> 00:24:21.050
And then the device
makers look at it

00:24:21.050 --> 00:24:22.342
like what can we do there?

00:24:22.342 --> 00:24:24.050
And then we get
involved, and we're like,

00:24:24.050 --> 00:24:26.088
oh, let's think how
the software works.

00:24:26.088 --> 00:24:28.130
And so that's kind of a
pretty consistent pattern

00:24:28.130 --> 00:24:28.922
of what we've seen.

00:24:28.922 --> 00:24:32.150
So we would have seen flexible
displays a couple of years

00:24:32.150 --> 00:24:35.390
ago from the display
manufacturers.

00:24:35.390 --> 00:24:38.090
And then a year or two later,
we would see device makers

00:24:38.090 --> 00:24:39.030
trying things out.

00:24:39.030 --> 00:24:40.573
And then we would get involved.

00:24:40.573 --> 00:24:41.990
But you know, I
actually am pretty

00:24:41.990 --> 00:24:44.090
excited about the foldables.

00:24:44.090 --> 00:24:48.050
I think we've been talking
a lot about phones folding

00:24:48.050 --> 00:24:52.730
into tablets, and I think
there's roughly form factors.

00:24:52.730 --> 00:24:55.580
But actually I think
there's a lot more ideas

00:24:55.580 --> 00:24:58.460
still to come that will be
quite surprising that I'm

00:24:58.460 --> 00:25:00.540
pretty excited about.

00:25:00.540 --> 00:25:03.620
And so yeah, I'm just thinking
like this time next year there

00:25:03.620 --> 00:25:05.870
will be actually quite a few
cool things to talk about

00:25:05.870 --> 00:25:07.640
in that space.

00:25:07.640 --> 00:25:08.390
Yeah.

00:25:08.390 --> 00:25:10.397
Anyone else want to add?

00:25:10.397 --> 00:25:12.980
CHET HAASE: And then eventually
marketing people get involved,

00:25:12.980 --> 00:25:15.530
and they say, you know what,
how about not bendy phones?

00:25:15.530 --> 00:25:16.650
How about foldables?

00:25:16.650 --> 00:25:18.650
Better.

