your own teams.

00:27:23.710 --> 00:27:25.210
DAVE BURKE: That's
a great question.

00:27:31.200 --> 00:27:34.630
So I've been spending a lot of
time in the medical industry

00:27:34.630 --> 00:27:40.420
lately in hospitals, and the
striking thing that I notice

00:27:40.420 --> 00:27:43.930
is that when doctors
do rounds and whatnot,

00:27:43.930 --> 00:27:47.860
the striking thing I notice
is how balanced and, in fact,

00:27:47.860 --> 00:27:51.030
female-heavy, just to give
one angle of diversity, it is.

00:27:51.030 --> 00:27:52.120
And then I come back--

00:27:52.120 --> 00:27:55.300
these really strong,
smart doctors.

00:27:55.300 --> 00:27:58.667
And then I come back
to work and it really,

00:27:58.667 --> 00:28:00.250
the diversity in the
software industry

00:28:00.250 --> 00:28:01.870
is really quite skewed.

00:28:01.870 --> 00:28:04.240
And it's something
we have to fix.

00:28:04.240 --> 00:28:06.940
And it's not because
you live in a bubble

00:28:06.940 --> 00:28:08.440
and you can be like,
well, the world

00:28:08.440 --> 00:28:10.023
needs to be more
diverse or something.

00:28:10.023 --> 00:28:11.980
But this industry
specifically, like,

00:28:11.980 --> 00:28:14.350
we really do need to improve it.

00:28:14.350 --> 00:28:16.090
And so we have a
bunch of initiatives

00:28:16.090 --> 00:28:17.007
that we're working on.

00:28:17.007 --> 00:28:22.750
But fundamentally, we need
to get more diverse people

00:28:22.750 --> 00:28:27.550
into the hiring chain so
we can hire more people.

00:28:27.550 --> 00:28:30.180
One of the arguments-- we
spent a lot of time in Google

00:28:30.180 --> 00:28:33.137
in trying to increase
diversity both in the company

00:28:33.137 --> 00:28:33.970
and within our team.

00:28:33.970 --> 00:28:35.790
But it feels like a
bit of a zero sum game.

00:28:35.790 --> 00:28:37.885
So we're going to
try to do better.

00:28:37.885 --> 00:28:39.760
But then other companies
are going to suffer.

00:28:39.760 --> 00:28:45.023
Like we need to work at this
at a sort of an industry level.

00:28:45.023 --> 00:28:46.690
So that's just one
or two of the things.

00:28:46.690 --> 00:28:48.220
I think other
people on this panel

00:28:48.220 --> 00:28:50.637
should talk to this point,
too, because it's so important.

00:28:50.637 --> 00:28:52.330
I know a lot of
people have opinions.

00:28:52.330 --> 00:28:52.570
STEPHANIE CUTHBERTSON:
I can just

00:28:52.570 --> 00:28:54.570
say briefly, one of things
I was really proud of

